name: Nathanial Jacobs
profile_summary: The individual is a 35-year-old straight man who uses he/him/his pronouns and hails from Chicago, Illinois. He stands at 6'1" and is of White Caucasian ethnicity. Educated to graduate level at the University of California, he is now a screenwriter in the entertainment industry, based in Los Angeles. An ENTP on the MBTI, he speaks both English and Spanish and practices his humor and creativity through travelling, writing and stand-up comedy. His values are rooted in creativity, adventure, and humor. Agnostic and politically liberal, he doesn't smoke or do drugs, but occasionally enjoys a drink. He leads an active lifestyle and is a dog owner. Even though he doesn't have any children, he is looking to have some in the future. He's up for a long term, monogamous relationship. His zodiac sign is Pisces and he exercises actively.
preferences_summary: The user is looking for a woman aged between 27 and 40 years of age with a height ranging from 5'0'' to 6'0''. She preferably should not have children, albeit she should ideally have the desire to have them in the future. The female partner should identify as straight, occasionally drink, not smoke, and not use marijuana or drugs. Maintaining an active physical lifestyle is important to him. In terms of ethnicity, he is open to most ethnicities, with the exception being White Caucasian. Politically, she could be liberal, moderate, or not political at all. A woman working in the entertainment, art, or education industries would be his preference. His ideal partner should speak English, Spanish or both and shares the values of creativity, humor, and adventure. Preferred interests would be traveling, cooking, and dancing. Additionally, he would appreciate if her education level is either an undergraduate degree, graduate, or falls into the category 'other'.
